						               													<description>A world of knowledge... gallivanting the globe from your home or classroom. Expeditious expeditions of adventure in learning. A geography game played on an authentic and colorfully detailed world map. Fun and educational for teens and adults.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game comes with four different categories of card (flags, general, capitals, countries).  Players roll and move their pawn on a track.  Each space on the track represents the color of card that must be answered.  In order to move again on the same turn, players must answer their trivia cards correctly.  For flag cards, players are shown a country flag with three possible answers on them.  They must choose the correct answer to move again.  General cards ask various questions related to physical or social geography.  Country cards ask players to identify what country is being referred to on the map (each country of the world has been numbered on the board).  Finally, players must identify the capital city of a specified country when they land on a country card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To win the game, the player who lands on the finish space and answers one final trivia question correctly wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
